Testimonial.Text: When I cannot fall asleep, I turn on this app and am out within 5 minutes.
I have a very busy brain and can find it hard to unwind. Now a daily practice is actually so wonderful and healing for me.
Healpathy has changed my life in immeasurable ways. I am more resilient and feel so much more connected to myself.

questions.text: Do you often seek perfection in everything you do?
options: No, I prefer to be flexible and adaptive.

questions.text: Do you feel the need to help others, even at your own expense?
options: Yes, helping others is very important to me.
No, I prioritize my own needs first.

questions.text: Do you find it important to stand out and be recognized for your achievements?
options: Yes, I want to be admired.
No, I don't seek external validation.

questions.text: Do you often feel that you need to understand everything deeply and completely?
options: Yes, understanding is crucial for me.
No, I am okay with surface-level knowledge.

questions.text: Do you tend to avoid conflicts and seek peace in relationships?
Do you often feel a strong sense of fear about the future or uncertainties?
options: Yes, I worry about the future.
No, I am confident in facing uncertainties.

questions.text: Do you enjoy being spontaneous and experiencing new things without much planning?
options: No, I prefer to plan things out.

questions.text: Do you often feel the need to be in control and assert your power in situations?
options: Yes, I like to be in control.
No, I am comfortable with others taking charge.

questions.text: Do you feel driven to succeed and achieve your goals no matter what?
options: Yes, success is very important to me.
No, I am content with what I have.

questions.text: Do you focus on maintaining a positive image and being liked by others?
options: Yes, I care about how others perceive me.
No, I am true to myself regardless of others' opinions.

questions.text: Do you tend to be overly critical of yourself and others?
Do you often find yourself avoiding discomfort and seeking pleasure?
Do you feel a strong need to be needed and appreciated by others?
options: Yes, I want to be helpful.
No, I don't rely on others' appreciation.

questions.text: Do you feel most comfortable when things are predictable and secure?
Do you find it important to know and adhere to the rules?
options: No, I think rules can be flexible.

questions.text: Do you often feel the need to prove your worth through accomplishments?
options: Yes, I derive value from achievements.
No, I am content with who I am.

questions.text: Do you often find yourself detached from others, preferring solitude?
Do you tend to be calm and composed even in stressful situations?
Do you often find yourself thinking about what could go wrong?
options: No, I focus on the positives.

questions.text: Do you feel a strong desire to protect those you care about?
options: No, I believe in letting people handle their own challenges.

questions.text: Do you prefer to stick to traditions and established ways of doing things?
Do you often feel that you must be strong and avoid showing vulnerability?
options: No, I am comfortable showing vulnerability.

questions.text: Do you find joy in being productive and busy?
options: Yes, being productive makes me happy.
No, I value relaxation and downtime.

questions.text: Do you often feel the need to withdraw from social interactions to recharge?
options: No, I gain energy from being with others.

questions.text: Do you enjoy brainstorming and coming up with new ideas?
Do you feel responsible for fixing others' problems?
options: No, I let others handle their own issues.

questions.text: Do you have a strong desire to improve the world around you?
options: Yes, making a difference is important to me.
No, I focus on personal goals.

questions.text: Do you often feel restless and seek out new experiences?
Do you find it difficult to trust others easily?
options: Yes, trust is hard for me.

questions.text: Do you often feel the need to take charge in group situations?
options: No, I prefer others to lead.

questions.text: Do you seek to avoid pain and focus on positive experiences?
options: No, I confront pain when necessary.

questions.text: Do you feel a strong sense of duty and responsibility towards your commitments?
options: Yes, I take my commitments seriously.
No, I am more flexible with commitments.

questions.text: Do you often feel the need to be the best in what you do?
options: No, I am satisfied with good enough.

questions.text: Do you find it easy to adapt to change and go with the flow?
Do you feel energized by social interactions and being with others?
options: Yes, I gain energy from people.
No, I need time alone to recharge.

questions.text: Do you tend to overthink and analyze situations deeply?
options: No, I act on instinct more often.
